  "texts": [
    "Another solution to overcome the limitations of traditional and generic portfolio strategies considered in the recent literature is reinforcement learning (RL) using neural networks.",
    "This research direction argues for implementing RNN and conventional NN in reinforcement learning architecture to support investment decisions.",
    "The main element in this theory is the connection between agents and the environment (Sutton and Barto, 2018).",
    "As a fundamental component of the ML process, in RL theory, the agents are supported by NN to memorize and predict optimal decisions based on present information for an infinite number of actions and states (Wu et al., 2021).",
    "The environment then estimates the rewards from these actions to help agents learn for future decisions."
